<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-10-24T16:19:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-10-24T16:19:00-05:00" n="264" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d264">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">310.2/10–2445: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The United States Representative at the United
                                Nations</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Austin</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-10-24T16:19:00-05:00">October
                                    24, 1951—4:19 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>526. Be Italian Membership: Italian observer Guidotti on instructions saw
                            Gross this morning and voiced Italian Govt’s “keen disappointment” that
                            Guidotti had been told by Hickerson we had no suggestions to offer re
                            Italian membership beyond what Guidotti called, “undoubtedly useless”,
                            step of renewed <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> discussion membership
                            question. He said in tripartite declaration we had indicated we <pb facs="0387" n="365" xml:id="pg_365"/> would take all steps possible
                            to aid Italy and we should do just that even if it meant “stretching the
                            charter a little”.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Austin</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>